Subject: [PATCH] Add buildVariable: false to Arsenal config.yaml

Arsenal is a static-only family (Regular, Bold, Italic, BoldItalic) with
no variable font axes. Without buildVariable: false, the builder defaults
to attempting a variable font build which fails. Arsenal SC, which uses
the same upstream repo, already has this flag set.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 ofl/arsenal/config.yaml | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/ofl/arsenal/config.yaml b/ofl/arsenal/config.yaml
index 35aa90921..8e42f5b46 100644
--- a/ofl/arsenal/config.yaml
+++ b/ofl/arsenal/config.yaml
@@ -1,3 +1,4 @@
+buildVariable: false
 sources:
   - sources/Arsenal.glyphs
   - sources/Arsenal-Italic.glyphs
